        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Add multiple sinks to a logger.\\nI have not considered this for now, but it should be very easy to implement.\n\nI was mostly concerned about the typing of the sink field because changing it to an array or keyed list of sinks would likely be a breaking change.\n\nHowever, after reading your comment, I re-evaluated how to make what I want work without any changes to your PR, and I think there is a decent solution with some precedent. The logger Serilog in C# implements async logging with a dedicated async sink that takes as a parameter a list of sinks. So to achieve what I want I could just create a dedicated sink that directs logs to multiple other sinks. Im okay with this approach.",
